 ESOL teachers and students.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aAdult educationzGreat Britain. 0aCitizenshipxStudy and teachingzGreat Britain. 0aEnglish languagexStudy and teachingxForeign speakers. 0aImmigrantsxEducationzGreat Britain. 0aLanguage and culturezGreat Britain. 0aLanguage policyzGreat Britain. 0aSocial integrationxGovernment policyzGreat Britain. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Study & Teaching.2bisacsh  aESOL.  aEnglish teaching for immigrants.  aadult education.  abrokering.  acitizenship.  aidentity .  amigration.  amulticulturalism.  amultilingualism.1 aBaynham, Mike, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBryers, Dermot, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCallaghan, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCooke, Melanie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCooke, Melanie, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGray, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHepworth, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHussain, Roseena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMacdonald, Sheila, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoon, Pauline, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPeutrell, Rob, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPeutrell, Rob, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRoberts, Celia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSimpson, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVollmer, Stefan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabula